                <h1>Knights in D&D 5E: Background and Role</h1>
                <p>In Dungeons and Dragons 5E, a knight background signifies a noble warrior dedicated to upholding chivalric values such as honor, duty, and courage. Knights often serve a lord or protection of the realm, embodying the virtues of bravery and loyalty. Their unique abilities can include leadership skills, combat training, and access to noble resources.</p>
